text: The Millpond Plantation in Thomas County, Georgia near Thomasville was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1976. Its present main house was built during 1903-1905 and the complex was completed in 1910; its architects were noted Cleveland, Ohio architects Hubbell & Benes and landscape design was by Warren Manning. Its architecture is Mission/Spanish Revival. The listing included six contributing buildings and two contributing structures on .
